    AgencyDistItem Base class for Agency Payment Item and Agency Promise Item: Stores values to be applied to an invoice item as part of an Agency Cycle Distribution

    • Method Detail

      • hasDifference

        boolean hasDifference()
        Returns:
        true if an attempt to apply this payment item to an invoice item as part of an agency payment would generate a payment exception (eg: this payment item specifies a gross amount to apply that is different from the amount of the associated invoice item, or this payment item specifies a commission amount to apply that is different from what the system expects to be applied for the associated invoice item)

      • getNetDifferenceAmount

        MonetaryAmount getNetDifferenceAmount()
        Returns:
        the monetary difference between the net amount to apply based on this payment item and the actual expected net amount due on the invoice item associated with this payment item

      • getNetAmountToApply

        MonetaryAmount getNetAmountToApply()
        Returns:
        the Net Amount to be applied for this item, i.e., Gross Amount To Apply minus Commission Amount To Apply

      • isCommissionModifiable

        boolean isCommissionModifiable()
        Returns:

      • getItemCommissionToTarget

        @Nullable
ItemCommission getItemCommissionToTarget()
